  Source:
    Title: The Origin and Meaning of Hasidism
By: Martin Buber
---
Human existence is not merely the space in which symbols and sacraments
appear, and not merely the material with which they clothe themselves. The
real existence ofa human person can itself be symbol, itself be sacrament.
